com.rwhitear.nimbleRest.volumes

Class CreateVolume

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rwhitear.nimbleRest.volumes.CreateVolume

  • public class CreateVolume
extends java.lang.Object
    Create a volume on a Nimble array via its RESTful API. This volume creation operation will include parameters such as volume name, size, description, Performance policy to use, whether to use encryption and cache pinning.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    rwhitear@cisco.com

    • Method Detail

      • create

        public java.lang.String create(java.lang.String volumeName,
                               java.lang.String description,
                               java.lang.String perfPolicyID,
                               boolean dataEncryption,
                               java.lang.String volumeSizeGB,
                               boolean cachePinning)
                        throws org.apache.commons.httpclient.HttpException,
                               java.io.IOException
        Create a new Nimble volume.
        Parameters:
        volumeName - Name to be given to the new volume.
        description - Volume description.
        perfPolicyID - Performance policy ID. Use com.rwhitear.nimbleRest.performancePolicies.GetPerformancePolicies to retrieve this ID from the performance policy name if required.
        dataEncryption - Choose whether volume should be encrypted or not.
        volumeSizeGB - Volume size in GB. This value needs to be converted to MB before calling the Nimble REST API as it accepts only MB values.
        cachePinning - Should volume be pinned in cache?
        Returns:
        Right now, just returns the HTTP response for the request. Need to write in comprehensive error checking.
        Throws:
        org.apache.commons.httpclient.HttpException - HTTP request exception handling.
        java.io.IOException - HTTP request exception handling.
